# SqueegeeOS Architecture

**Mission:** Luxury home care platform — not a window cleaning CRM. Document the **life of a property**, not jobs.

## Product flow

```
Marketing Website → Home Care Assessment → Homeowner Portal → Property Hub → Property Dashboard → Property Timeline → Visits → Photos → AI Intelligence
```

Property Hub is where employee and homeowner journeys converge. Timeline is the spine; visits and photos feed it; AI enriches everything downstream.

**PWA:** Squeegeeking.net → member login → Add to Home Screen. Design customer pages mobile-first.

## Modules

Employee Dashboard · Technician App · Customer Home Care Portal · AI Engine · Property Timeline · Membership System · Proposal Generator · Photo Library · Annual Home Care Review · Admin Dashboard

## Core model

- **Homeowner** → many **Properties** (each fully independent)
- **Property** owns: Home Care Score, Membership, Timeline, Photo Library, AI summaries, technician notes, recommendations, services, proposals, documents, agreements, before/after photos, visit history, access info, custom notes
- **Property Timeline** is critical: every visit auto-creates an entry (date, technician, photos, notes, AI summary, services, score changes, recommendations, customer summary)

## Technician flow

Arrive → tap property → upload photos → check services → quick notes → Finish Visit. AI handles notes, summary, score, recommendations, follow-up email/text, portal update.

## Customer portal

Apple Photos × luxury real estate portfolio. Property-specific routes: `/homecare/[homeowner]/[property]`. Dark luxury aesthetic.

## People & team content

**All customer-facing people must be real Squeegeeking team members or clearly marked portrait placeholders. Never stock photos or fictional names.**

- Founders: Noah Thomas, Dasan Gramps — `lib/team/founders.ts`
- Portraits: `public/team/{slug}/portrait-*.webp` — auto-replaces placeholders site-wide
- Components: `components/team/` (`FounderPortrait`, `FounderProfileCard`, `MeetTheFounders`)

## Nav (built)

`/` ↔ `/properties` ↔ `/properties/[slug]` ↔ `/properties/[slug]/home-care-plan`

